Benefits of Cloud Pricing:

High Avalibility: Avaliable all time with small outrages
Scalability: 
Cloud scalability allows businesses to dynamically adjust computing resources—scaling up during peak demand and scaling down when workloads decrease—ensuring efficiency, cost savings, and uninterrupted performance. It is one of the most critical advantages of cloud computing, especially for organizations in fast-growing markets like India where demand can fluctuate rapidly
Elasticity:
Azure elasticity provides cost savings, performance optimization, and scalability by automatically adjusting resources based on demand. This ensures you only pay for what you use, while maintaining consistent performance during peak loads
Realibility:
Azure reliability ensures that your applications and data remain available, resilient, and consistent even during failures or unexpected demand spikes. It provides high availability, disaster recovery, and confidence in running mission-critical workloads.
Predictability:
Azure predictability is about giving organizations confidence in their cloud costs, performance, and operations. It ensures that workloads behave consistently, budgets remain under control, and IT teams can plan ahead without surprises.
Security:
Azure security benefits organizations by protecting data, applications, and infrastructure with a multilayered defense approach, ensuring compliance, threat detection, and rapid response to cyber incidents. It reduces risks from evolving cyber threats while giving businesses confidence to run workloads securely
Governanace:
Azure governance benefits organizations by providing structure, control, and accountability in how cloud resources are managed. It ensures compliance, cost control, and consistent operations across teams and workloads.
Managability: 
Azure manageability benefits organizations by simplifying how cloud resources are deployed, monitored, updated, and scaled. It reduces manual effort, improves consistency, and ensures IT teams can manage workloads efficiently across on-premises, hybrid, and cloud environments.